Located in Chicago, Illinois with a 161-acre urban campus the university enrolls over 3,000 students with 2,100+ undergraduate students and nearly 900 graduate students. The university has a diverse student body that represents 38 states, 20 Illinois counties and 12 countries.

College_Heading: Jacksonville University: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: Jacksonville University (JU) ranks #31 in the Best Regional Universities in the Southern USA by US News & World Report. As a private institution in Florida, it offers more than 100 bachelors, masters, and doctoral degrees. Avila University: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: Avila University is a catholic university providing liberal arts, professional, undergraduate, and graduate programs. It has quite a competitive admission policy with a less than 50% acceptance rate. Some popular majors offered by the university include Business Administration, Computer Science, Graphic Design, Marketing, Communication, MBA, etc. The university has a total enrollment of 1,413 enrolled students including 1,057 undergraduates and 356 graduates seeking to study in the USA. The university invites applications on a rolling basis as there are no formal deadlines. However, international applicants must start the application process as soon as possible to receive timely admission decisions and complete the visa procedure.

College_Heading: University of Nebraska - Kearney, USA: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: University of Nebraska - Kearney is a public institution that initially began as Nebraska State Normal School in 1905 and emerged into its present form in 1991. The university serves 6,200+ students and is currently home to 5,274 undergraduate students and 1,628 graduate students. More than 300 international students representing 50 countries add diversity to the student body. The university is located in the heart of Kearney and offers quality education with more than 170 majors and programs at the undergraduate, graduate, and pre-professional levels. Programs of the university are organized into 3 colleges of Arts and Science, Education, Business and Technology.
